Subject: [PATCH 106/106] Fix zeromq libdir path on some systems.

If you specify --libdir-name argument then this is not propigated
through correctly to zeromq's configure script.
---
 mythtv/configure | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/mythtv/configure b/mythtv/configure
index 1e53650..100dff3 100755
--- a/mythtv/configure
+++ b/mythtv/configure
@@ -6501,6 +6501,7 @@
     fi
     (cd external/zeromq ; \
              ./configure --quiet --without-documentation --prefix=${prefix} \
+	     		 --libdir=${libdir_default} \
                          --includedir=${prefix}/include/mythtv/zeromq)
     echo "Configuring nzmqt..."
     (cd external/nzmqt/src ; \
